Input Validation Implementation (P1.19-P1.27):

WHY: Users were getting cryptic AWS SDK errors when providing invalid config
values (wrong CPU/memory combos, invalid ports, bad regions). Validating
inputs early provides clear, actionable error messages.

VALIDATIONS IMPLEMENTED:

P1.19 - Fargate CPU/Memory:
- validFargateConfigs map defines all valid combinations per AWS docs
- Error message lists valid memory values for the given CPU

P1.20 - Log Retention:
- validLogRetentionDays map with CloudWatch-accepted values
- Wired into createInfra before provisioning

P1.23 - Container Port:
- Range check 1-65535
- Wired into deploy

P1.24 - Environment Variables:
- Regex: ^[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$
- Blocks AWS_, ECS_, FARGATE_ prefixes (reserved)
- Wired into deploy

P1.25 - Health Check Path:
- Must start with / (or empty for default)
- Wired into deploy

P1.26 - AWS Region:
- validAWSRegions map with major regions
- Wired into planInfra

P1.27 - Desired Count:
- Range 1-100 (prevents runaway costs)
- Higher counts require auto-scaling

TESTING: 100+ test cases covering edge cases for all validations
